      "title": "Mutating Bash can bypass plan/test review triggers entirely",
      "evidence": "The Bash pretrigger only treats production .go and .tdd audit/exception paths as gated, explicitly excluding *_test.go and never matching .tdd/current-plan.md, .tdd/plans/**, or docs/specs/*.md. The PostToolUse backstop also skips *_test.go, .tdd/*, docs/*, and specs/*, so commands like `printf ... > internal/foo_test.go` or `cat > .tdd/current-plan.md` land without TEST_REVIEW_REQUIRED/PLAN_REVIEW_REQUIRED and without a pending obligation.",
      "recommendation": "Extend both Bash pretrigger and posttool detection to the same path universe as the Edit/Write triggers, or deny all mutating Bash writes to gated paths and require Edit/Write/MultiEdit so the primary triggers run.",
