      "title": "Review completions can be accepted with unscoped legacy audit rows",
      "evidence": "Plan completion validation falls back from strict `obligation_completed` scope/review_type matching to any audit line containing the candidate exception_id, and then accepts empty `prev_audit_sha`. Review-completion entries are new v1.9 artifacts, so this legacy path lets a forged approved completion plus a weak audit row satisfy the hook without runner-written scope binding.",
      "recommendation": "Remove legacy audit fallback for plan_review_completion, test_review_completion, and production_edit_review_completion. Require an `obligation_completed` row with matching exception_id, cycle_id, review_type, scope_hash, and a valid prev_sha chain link before allowing.",
