      "severity": "P0",
      "category": "correctness",
      "title": "Production drift approvals are shadowed by the original completion",
      "evidence": "The production trigger selects the first approved completion whose scope_hash is either the normal production scope or the drift scope. Drift pending entries are appended after the original completion and the runner updates them in place, so retrying a drift-approved edit still selects the original normal-scope entry first and denies PRODUCTION_SCOPE_DRIFT again.",
      "recommendation": "Prefer the exact drift scope_hash for the current file before considering the broad production scope, or filter matched entries by allowed_file_globs before choosing one.",
      "location": ".claude/hooks/second-opinion-production-trigger.sh:104"
